                I used <br>
                <b>HTML, CSS, JavaScript, Bootstrap, jQuery, AngularJS and Ajax</b> for the
                front-end to display the records, the form for creating the records
                and to pass the inputted data to the server.<br>
                <b>C# and LINQ</b> to insert and retrieve data from the database, as
                well as sending the notification as an email.
            </blockquote>
            <p>
                My team leader was satisfied with the features I included in the pages
                and the extra effort I spent in order to meet the deadline of the
                project. Now the job of creating a maintenance notification can easily
                be done by an employee from a different team and the Application
                Development Team can focus on other projects or the details of the
                deployment.
